1
00:00:14,590 --> 00:00:16,240
Wanna stop by the store?

2
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:19,040
- I know it's cold, but ice cream would...
- Ouji.

3
00:00:20,570 --> 00:00:25,020
I want to have sex with you.

4
00:00:39,220 --> 00:00:40,860
Erm...

5
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,340
Oreo.

6
00:00:46,340 --> 00:00:47,810
Come here, boy!

7
00:00:47,810 --> 00:00:48,940
Sorry to bother.

8
00:00:48,940 --> 00:00:50,960
- It's fine.
- No worries.

9
00:00:58,110 --> 00:01:02,100
Let's just get home, yeah?

10
00:01:03,610 --> 00:01:06,280
Okay. Yeah.

11
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:17,420
<i>Dragging me by the arm?</i>

12
00:01:33,250 --> 00:01:38,650
<i>Can it be? Can I expect something tonight?</i>

13
00:01:38,650 --> 00:01:40,720
Should we open a bottle?

14
00:01:43,030 --> 00:01:46,280
- What's up?
- How do you make tea?

15
00:01:46,280 --> 00:01:48,080
Tea?

16
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:51,970
First, you have to brew the water.

17
00:01:51,970 --> 00:01:54,770
Right. The water.

18
00:01:57,030 --> 00:01:58,990
Tea?

19
00:02:07,700 --> 00:02:15,030
Am I... being rejected right now?

20
00:02:15,690 --> 00:02:17,390
Listen.

21
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:22,560
I was equally as happy, you know?

22
00:02:25,420 --> 00:02:28,540
To hug you and all.

23
00:02:31,770 --> 00:02:35,610
I just felt awkward saying it.

24
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,970
The thing is...

25
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:48,760
I actually love you, Haru.

26
00:02:52,330 --> 00:02:58,910
I know we married on the fly,
and got the order all wrong, but...

27
00:03:09,410 --> 00:03:10,890
Haru?

28
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,620
I'm so relieved.

29
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,810
I feel so happy right now.

30
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:39,620
I...

31
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:44,960
I've been waiting to hear those words...

32
00:03:47,210 --> 00:03:50,900
All this time.

33
00:03:55,670 --> 00:04:00,690
Ouji, I...

34
00:04:41,360 --> 00:04:43,180
I love you, too.

35
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,990
I'm sorry.

36
00:06:21,190 --> 00:06:25,310
[Episode 5]

37
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:38,270
[Heading out to a meeting]

38
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:45,770
Their mini album will be released
after the concert.

39
00:06:45,770 --> 00:06:49,920
We'll decide the number of songs
at a later date.

40
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:51,670
As for next year's agenda...

41
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:10,420
Marriage ain't so easy after all, right?

42
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,600
Huh?

43
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,330
At least, that's what your face is saying.

44
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,010
What's that supposed to mean?

45
00:07:16,010 --> 00:07:17,730
Quit making assumptions.

46
00:07:17,730 --> 00:07:22,260
On the brink of a divorce
after you were caught cheating?

47
00:07:22,260 --> 00:07:23,440
Hell no.

48
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,010
Yeah, I don't think that's it.

49
00:07:25,010 --> 00:07:27,920
Ouji's changed ever since he married Haru.

50
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,700
It's like he's mellowed out.

51
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,880
That'll help improve our image.

52
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:35,760
Right? Coincidence or not, I'll take it.

53
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:39,420
Haru's got a compelling power like that.

54
00:07:39,420 --> 00:07:40,860
I know.

55
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:44,390
Huh, you're actually serious about her.

56
00:07:44,390 --> 00:07:46,240
I said, quit making assumptions.

57
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:48,230
We have to. You won't tell us a thing,

58
00:07:48,230 --> 00:07:50,300
even after two decades of playing together.

59
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:54,670
Then you two know Haru as well as I do.

60
00:07:54,670 --> 00:07:57,390
You're asking about our thoughts on Haru?

61
00:07:57,390 --> 00:08:01,060
Well, I remember she'd wait for us
after shows and before recordings.

62
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:04,080
She was a groupie, or practically a stalk...

63
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,810
Haru isn't...

64
00:08:06,790 --> 00:08:08,530
She isn't like that.

65
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:17,470
We're considering solo activities as well.

66
00:08:17,470 --> 00:08:19,460
And you, Tanaka?

67
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:23,710
Ouji.

68
00:08:23,710 --> 00:08:26,660
I think that individual
works for a tabloid magazine.

69
00:08:26,660 --> 00:08:27,800
I've seen them around before.

70
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:31,330
Seriously? What a pain.

71
00:08:31,330 --> 00:08:33,090
Guess the party's over.

72
00:08:38,130 --> 00:08:42,240
Hamburger steaks, huh? My favorite.

73
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,830
Holy cow, that's good.

74
00:08:54,320 --> 00:08:56,210
Let's just get married.

75
00:08:57,270 --> 00:08:59,490
WHAT?

76
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:05,440
That hurts... Why?

77
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,520
Wait, this is real?

78
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:10,420
Of course it's real.

79
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:19,980
Hey, no more crying, okay?

80
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,890
Ow, ouch.

81
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:26,580
Welcome back!

82
00:09:27,470 --> 00:09:29,060
I'm home.

83
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:34,820
Good night! Sweet dreams!

84
00:09:51,010 --> 00:09:55,950
I do actually love her.

85
00:09:57,050 --> 00:10:00,100
Your expression says otherwise.

86
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:03,500
- Huh?
- Yeah, why the dissatisfied look?

87
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:08,110
I'm not dissatisfied, it's just...

88
00:10:08,110 --> 00:10:09,940
I love her.

89
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:13,400
Which is exactly why it's not so simple.

90
00:10:14,820 --> 00:10:19,640
Ouji. I think you're overthinking it.

91
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:24,630
This is your first crush,
and your first marriage.

92
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:28,790
Of course you're confused.

93
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:33,820
- Well...
- If you love her, take it a step at a time.

94
00:10:35,870 --> 00:10:39,480
If only I could.

95
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:43,050
What, so you just wanted to brag?

96
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:45,660
Man, I want to get married, too.

97
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:48,180
Your first step is to quit four-timing.
[Keiko Kotani]

98
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,620
I'm serious about all of them!
[Can we meet later today?]

99
00:10:50,620 --> 00:10:54,170
Trash. You utter scumbag.

100
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:04,430
- Haru, are you hungry?
- Huh?

101
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:05,680
Was my stomach growling?

102
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:09,980
No, but there's a taco rice truck out front.
How about it?

103
00:11:09,980 --> 00:11:12,790
Sorry, but I'm grabbing lunch
with some friends today.

104
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,960
Ah, I see.

105
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:17,610
I'm free to grab a quick coffee, though.

106
00:11:17,610 --> 00:11:22,050
I finished writing my draft early today.

107
00:11:22,050 --> 00:11:24,100
Inspiration's flowing?

108
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:29,110
Yeah. I overcame a hurdle of some sort.

109
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:33,600
Oh? That's good to hear.

110
00:11:33,600 --> 00:11:35,550
Should we get going?

111
00:11:35,550 --> 00:11:37,740
No, let's shelve it for another day.

112
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:40,260
I'd rather try it out with you.

113
00:11:40,260 --> 00:11:41,900
If you insist.

114
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:47,840
Didn't realize you were
such a fan of taco rice.

115
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,340
You could say that.

116
00:11:49,340 --> 00:11:51,110
Wow.

117
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:08,200
[Ouji]

118
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,390
<i>Sorry, I'll be late tonight.</i>

119
00:12:17,130 --> 00:12:21,440
Haru. It's a bit creepy seeing you
grinning in the streets like that.

120
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:25,960
<i>Roger!</i>

121
00:12:37,500 --> 00:12:39,780
- Fuyumi!
- There you are!

122
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:41,700
Thanks for waiting.

123
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,650
Drinking while the sun's still up?

124
00:12:47,650 --> 00:12:50,870
Yup. I already finished work for the day.

125
00:12:50,870 --> 00:12:55,350
Wait, that can't be the only reason
you're beaming.

126
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:57,140
Haru, you haven't told her yet?

127
00:12:57,140 --> 00:13:01,050
I thought she'd be a bit exasperated,
hearing me gloat.

128
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:02,660
Already am.

129
00:13:02,660 --> 00:13:04,180
Thought so.

130
00:13:04,900 --> 00:13:08,030
Okay, here me out.

131
00:13:10,340 --> 00:13:12,630
- A hug...
- A confession...

132
00:13:12,630 --> 00:13:15,160
And then another hug?

133
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,030
Yup.

134
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:21,680
Cheers!

135
00:13:23,090 --> 00:13:27,010
Your drink must taste all the sweeter, Haru.

136
00:13:27,010 --> 00:13:31,600
Such pure love at your age... Savor it!

137
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:36,220
Thank you two for always listening.

138
00:13:36,220 --> 00:13:39,490
Then I bet you're raring to go home tonight?

139
00:13:39,490 --> 00:13:43,190
No, Ouji says work is keeping him late today.

140
00:13:43,190 --> 00:13:45,930
Gosh, I'm a bit miffed after all!

141
00:13:45,930 --> 00:13:50,820
I know we did things in the wrong order.

142
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:53,690
But now that we've reaffirmed our feelings,

143
00:13:53,690 --> 00:13:55,460
I feel absolutely fulfilled.

144
00:13:55,460 --> 00:13:59,310
I suppose order doesn't matter after all.

145
00:13:59,310 --> 00:14:01,780
Sure, he still lacks a sex drive.

146
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:05,170
But it doesn't seem like
such an obstacle anymore.

147
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:08,410
We'll overcome that wall, together.

148
00:14:08,410 --> 00:14:11,600
You're grinning wide. Cute!

149
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:19,760
I'm sure Akina's thinking love is pointless
without the sex, though.

150
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:24,180
No, I think it's a wonderful development.

151
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:27,810
- What?
- If you're certain he loves you,

152
00:14:27,810 --> 00:14:32,620
then maybe you can hold off on sex after all.

153
00:14:32,620 --> 00:14:35,300
Huh? Who are you?

154
00:14:35,300 --> 00:14:37,080
What did you to do our Akina?

155
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:42,560
Let's just say I met someone
who changed my mind.

156
00:14:42,560 --> 00:14:44,140
What?

157
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:46,860
- A platonic love?
- Wow...

158
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:49,240
I didn't realize platonic feelings
were contagious.

159
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:52,930
No, I don't feel a platonic love for him.

160
00:14:52,930 --> 00:14:56,240
And we've done everything but go all the way.

161
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:59,250
- Erotic as that may sound.
- Woah.

162
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:06,840
Anyway, I sort of understand how you felt
when you first met Ouji.

163
00:15:09,490 --> 00:15:13,930
<i>Let us both enjoy our time together.</i>

164
00:15:13,930 --> 00:15:18,170
<i>He made me think, "he's the one"...</i>

165
00:15:18,170 --> 00:15:20,620
Type of relationship be damned.

166
00:15:21,210 --> 00:15:23,110
I see.

167
00:15:23,110 --> 00:15:25,730
To think even Akina would find someone.

168
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:27,610
So what's he like?

169
00:15:27,610 --> 00:15:29,900
Is he a foreign dude?

170
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:32,080
His face sort of looks like it.

171
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,450
He kinda gives "K-pop idol" vibes...

172
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:36,220
No, a boxer.

173
00:15:36,220 --> 00:15:37,850
You're confusing us.

174
00:15:37,850 --> 00:15:41,450
More importantly,
his mannerisms are to die for!

175
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:44,320
He's usually the courteous type, except...

176
00:15:44,320 --> 00:15:47,760
What's the matter, Akina?

177
00:15:54,060 --> 00:15:56,750
I hate being the only one who's feeling it.

178
00:15:57,460 --> 00:16:00,840
I want to make you feel good, too.

179
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:05,300
- Huh?
- We're allowed to go halfway, right?

180
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,760
I'm confident in my skills.

181
00:16:10,390 --> 00:16:16,350
I'd be tempted to stay,
so that'll have to be a "nope" from me.

182
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:20,600
What? What is it?

183
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:22,280
Give us an example.

184
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:25,420
He'll drop the courtesy, without warning.

185
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:27,970
Why is that so effective?

186
00:16:27,970 --> 00:16:29,680
I get it!

187
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:30,810
You do, Fuyumi?

188
00:16:30,810 --> 00:16:35,530
I love getting a glimpse
of their true colors.

189
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:38,650
- It makes my heart squeeze!
- I'm the opposite.

190
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:41,190
I love the professionalism
of keeping an appropriate distance.

191
00:16:41,190 --> 00:16:43,070
"Professionalism"?

192
00:16:43,070 --> 00:16:46,550
- It's just an example.
- Nicknames are great, too.

193
00:16:46,550 --> 00:16:52,560
Going from "hey you",
to a cute nickname? It's the best!

194
00:16:52,560 --> 00:16:54,190
Sounds like a player. Sorry, can't relate.

195
00:16:54,190 --> 00:16:56,920
Don't get rational on me now.

196
00:16:56,920 --> 00:17:01,960
Going from "Ms." to first name basis
is what gets me.

197
00:17:01,960 --> 00:17:06,040
Name-calling in bed is pretty great, too.

198
00:17:08,150 --> 00:17:12,420
Our preferences are all over the place,

199
00:17:12,420 --> 00:17:17,350
but we're ultimately charmed
by these people, huh?

200
00:17:17,350 --> 00:17:22,560
Personally, I'm fulfilled
just hearing your stories.

201
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:24,890
Do our stories entertain you?

202
00:17:24,890 --> 00:17:28,160
Yes, they're almost too stimulating.

203
00:17:31,610 --> 00:17:33,550
Jeez...

204
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:37,580
[An article next week will report a scandal]

205
00:17:37,580 --> 00:17:39,340
[between a stage play actor and our staff]

206
00:17:40,910 --> 00:17:42,700
What happened?

207
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:44,200
Fuyumi?

208
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,840
Fuyumi?

209
00:17:46,960 --> 00:17:49,670
[Apparently, his partner's a makeup artist]

210
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,580
[An article next week will report a scandal]

211
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:54,870
[between a stage play actor and our staff]

212
00:17:58,530 --> 00:18:00,620
Is everything okay?

213
00:18:05,160 --> 00:18:09,320
Someone at the elementary school
was afflicted with food poisoning.

214
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:12,540
I-I'm sure Chizuka is fine, but...

215
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:15,920
I'm sorry. I need to go hear the details.

216
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,750
- Okay.
- Don't worry about paying.

217
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:19,530
- Hurry.
- Sorry, thank you.

218
00:18:19,530 --> 00:18:21,190
Take care!

219
00:18:44,650 --> 00:18:46,000
[Shota]

220
00:18:54,660 --> 00:18:57,450
[Shota]
[Please give me a call]

221
00:18:57,450 --> 00:18:58,940
[Have you heard?]
[About the article]

222
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:03,930
I shouldn't leave any evidence.

223
00:19:05,860 --> 00:19:08,110
No, it's too late now.

224
00:19:08,110 --> 00:19:09,040
[Delete message]

225
00:19:09,040 --> 00:19:11,320
[Shota]

226
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:13,760
Shota?

227
00:19:13,760 --> 00:19:15,780
<i>Fuyumi...</i>

228
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:18,980
Did you hear the news? About the article.

229
00:19:18,980 --> 00:19:24,240
I did. An affair. Could it be...

230
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,430
I wonder how we were found out.

231
00:19:26,430 --> 00:19:27,670
What?

232
00:19:27,670 --> 00:19:31,860
We always met at my place, right?

233
00:19:31,860 --> 00:19:34,100
<i>We never went in at the same time, too.</i>

234
00:19:34,100 --> 00:19:37,580
And I made sure to keep
an appropriate distance at work.

235
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:40,080
- That might be it.
- Huh?

236
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:44,710
We may have acted too close.

237
00:19:45,560 --> 00:19:48,980
What should I do?

238
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:51,650
I'm sorry.

239
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:54,520
<i>Shota, I...</i>

240
00:19:56,880 --> 00:19:58,590
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

241
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:01,960
Don't apologize, Fuyumi.

242
00:20:03,650 --> 00:20:07,150
I'm the one who fell for you first.

243
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:10,040
But I'm the adult. I work backstage.

244
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:13,760
No more of that, okay?

245
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,350
I want you to see me as your equal.

246
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:21,930
If the article is published,

247
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:28,560
I'll say I insisted on pursuing something.

248
00:20:29,460 --> 00:20:31,680
Tell them you couldn't turn me down.

249
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:33,020
Why would you...

250
00:20:33,020 --> 00:20:34,960
Because I want to protect you.

251
00:20:36,870 --> 00:20:38,990
Though I may be younger,

252
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,900
I'm a man, first and foremost.

253
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:53,530
My manager's calling.

254
00:20:53,530 --> 00:20:58,040
I'll text again if I learn something new.

255
00:20:59,040 --> 00:21:00,520
Okay.

256
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:13,460
<i>I'm sorry I got worked up.</i>

257
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:18,620
<i>Chizuka was fine, as are the other kids.</i>

258
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:20,480
Thank goodness.

259
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:24,800
Seriously, she looked so worried
when she left.

260
00:21:25,580 --> 00:21:28,690
She really is a mother, isn't she?

261
00:21:28,690 --> 00:21:30,520
She sure is.

262
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:34,470
Alright. Now that we know Chizuka's okay,

263
00:21:34,470 --> 00:21:37,220
how about we go for karaoke?

264
00:21:37,220 --> 00:21:40,260
I've had enough secondhand happiness
for the day.

265
00:21:40,260 --> 00:21:41,890
Besides, I have plans.

266
00:21:41,890 --> 00:21:45,410
But I still have lots to share...

267
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,140
Wait, is it a date?

268
00:21:48,140 --> 00:21:49,900
With Mr. Eros?

269
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:53,040
You could say that.

270
00:21:54,820 --> 00:21:57,850
You're poking fun at me like an old man.

271
00:22:04,140 --> 00:22:07,370
<i>If we've got extra time afterwards,
care to join me for a drink?</i>

272
00:22:10,290 --> 00:22:13,940
<i>Sounds good. But will we have extra time?</i>

273
00:22:13,940 --> 00:22:16,640
<i>So long as I don't feel too good.</i>

274
00:22:17,780 --> 00:22:19,710
<i>Then it seems we'll have no time after all.</i>

275
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:24,030
Confident, isn't he?

276
00:22:40,770 --> 00:22:42,240
Huh?

277
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:09,410
[Heading out to a meeting]

278
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:14,430
Welcome home!

279
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:19,760
Ouji?

280
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:22,550
What's wrong?

281
00:23:23,230 --> 00:23:24,750
Haru.

282
00:23:27,670 --> 00:23:29,070
I'm sorry.

283
00:23:34,070 --> 00:23:36,670
- Ouji?
- Let's break up.

284
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:58,300
[Preview]

